27:47.056 --> 27:50.494
that guy I collared from the
Beame Complex looked familiar?

27:50.538 --> 27:52.627
We collared a hundred people
from the Beame Complex, Eddie.

27:52.671 --> 27:53.628
No, no.

27:53.672 --> 27:55.064
Absolutely not.
Just hold 'em

27:55.108 --> 27:56.326
outside in the vans,
all right?

27:56.370 --> 27:58.764
This is the guy
that jumped out the window.

27:58.807 --> 28:01.201
What?
He's a murderer.

28:06.597 --> 28:08.687
Eddie, what the hell
are you talking about?

28:08.730 --> 28:11.690
Remember the Bushwick Butcher,
maniac who hacked up that family

28:11.733 --> 28:13.169
last summer?Of course I remember, yeah.

28:13.213 --> 28:14.823
NYPD tracked down
the case for months.

28:14.867 --> 28:17.347
All we ended up with was some
DNA we couldn't find a match to.

28:17.391 --> 28:20.655
And a composite sketch
from the surviving victim.

28:20.699 --> 28:24.703
Bushwick Butcher, my guy.

28:33.102 --> 28:35.539
When does it end?

28:35.583 --> 28:38.629
When law and order is
restored, that's when it ends.

28:38.673 --> 28:40.588
You're disrupting,
not restoring.

28:40.631 --> 28:42.024
Well...

28:42.068 --> 28:44.200
You just don't get it.

28:44.244 --> 28:45.854
That makes millions of us.

28:45.898 --> 28:48.161
Who what? Who didn't like the
pictures they saw on television?

28:48.204 --> 28:50.163
Sorry about that.
Couldn't be helped.

28:50.206 --> 28:52.992
And your attitude's almost
as troubling as your actions.

28:53.035 --> 28:54.645
Garrett, could we just
call it a day

28:54.689 --> 28:56.169
before I call security on you?

28:56.212 --> 28:57.953
Then call 'em and toss me out.

28:57.997 --> 28:59.999
But until then,
I'm right here doing my job.

29:00.042 --> 29:01.261
As the back seat driver.

29:01.304 --> 29:03.089
As the one guy
who's gonna say

29:03.132 --> 29:05.134
enough with the shock and awe.

29:05.178 --> 29:07.223
What you're doing is not serving
public interest.

29:07.267 --> 29:12.185
Look, I can't just issue
press releases condemning thugs.

29:12.228 --> 29:14.230
I have to take measures,
and I am.

29:14.274 --> 29:17.059
I know. You don't care
what anybody else thinks.

29:17.103 --> 29:18.844
Oh, yeah, I do.

29:18.887 --> 29:20.802
I care about a classroom
full of kids

29:20.846 --> 29:22.456
who can't get an education

29:22.499 --> 29:24.023
'cause their teacher's
too scared

29:24.066 --> 29:25.807
of the hoods in the back row.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.809
The silent majority?
They're back?

29:27.853 --> 29:29.811
They never left.

29:29.855 --> 29:32.901
And they saw what that crowd did
to our cops.

29:32.945 --> 29:35.208
And they go,
"If they can act that way

29:35.251 --> 29:37.253
toward police officers,
what about us?"

29:37.297 --> 29:38.298
What about

29:38.341 --> 29:39.952
the mom who has to race

29:39.995 --> 29:42.911
across that lobby just
to protect her frightened kids,

29:42.955 --> 29:45.479
or the old lady who's afraid
to go for groceries?

29:45.522 --> 29:46.654
Then make that case!

29:46.697 --> 29:48.090
I just did.

29:48.134 --> 29:51.441
How?
Actions speak louder
than words.

29:51.485 --> 29:53.095
And what's that from--
The Art of War?

29:53.139 --> 29:55.141
No. Abe Lincoln said it first.

30:09.546 --> 30:11.331
You got a minute, Captain?

30:11.374 --> 30:13.550
Think you're gonna
want to see this.

30:14.900 --> 30:16.858
Remember this guy?

30:16.902 --> 30:19.556
I do. The Bushwick Butcher.

30:19.600 --> 30:22.559
Looks a lot like
this guy, doesn't he?

30:22.603 --> 30:23.909
Who is he?

30:23.952 --> 30:25.475
John Mendoza. He
was one of the crew

30:25.519 --> 30:26.999
that bullied our cops.
The camera man.

30:27.042 --> 30:28.783
Geez.

30:28.827 --> 30:30.611
Yeah, luckily, we got
a second crack at him.

30:30.654 --> 30:32.700
Officer Janko collared him
when we took the Beame Complex.

30:32.743 --> 30:34.397
Put a cop on that cell ASAP.

30:34.441 --> 30:36.573
I don't want this guy
getting lost in our chaos.Already done.

30:36.617 --> 30:38.880
And contact the detective
who worked this case.

30:38.924 --> 30:41.970
I'm sure they had DNA left
behind at one of the murders.

30:42.014 --> 30:43.972
Detective Larkin
is on his way.

30:44.016 --> 30:46.192
Also, Officer Janko gave
the perp a cup of water,

30:46.235 --> 30:49.325
then sealed it in an envelope
when he was done drinking it.

30:49.369 --> 30:50.631
Lab's running the
DNA right now.

30:50.674 --> 30:52.154
This is damn good work,
Sergeant.

30:52.198 --> 30:53.503
All Officer Janko, sir.

30:53.547 --> 30:55.636
I'll make sure
to give her my thanks.

30:55.679 --> 30:57.290
Captain.

30:57.333 --> 30:59.031
You know, Reagan,

30:59.074 --> 31:02.121
there are a lot of folks
at this precinct

31:02.164 --> 31:06.168
that are gonna be better cops
because of your leadership.

31:06.212 --> 31:08.214
Including me.

31:11.347 --> 31:13.784
Boss.

31:13.828 --> 31:15.612
Jordan Amendola.

31:15.656 --> 31:17.310
August 2016.

31:17.353 --> 31:21.096
Bobby Katz, September 2016.

31:21.140 --> 31:25.405
Jamal Richardson, January 2018.

31:25.448 --> 31:28.321
Harry Dunn, March 2018.

31:28.364 --> 31:31.324
Lawrence Indigo.

31:31.367 --> 31:33.326
June 2018.

31:33.369 --> 31:36.372
All five of them murdered
with the gun that you had
in your possession.

31:36.416 --> 31:39.636
Each time the trigger was pulled
by a different person.

31:39.680 --> 31:41.682
Nick Tedesco.

31:43.118 --> 31:44.685
Matt Kleeber.

31:45.686 --> 31:47.470
Roddy Mack.

31:48.254 --> 31:50.125
Rich Leeds.

31:50.169 --> 31:54.608
And the guy who gave you
the gun, Jimmy Matson.

31:54.651 --> 31:56.915
You know all five
of these killers

31:56.958 --> 31:59.308
because they were all
Trip Treys, am I right?

31:59.352 --> 32:02.007
Yeah.
And you can
only become

32:02.050 --> 32:05.227
a Trip Trey if you
kill someone yourself.

32:05.271 --> 32:07.403
Anyone. Randomly.

32:07.447 --> 32:08.927
Am I right?

32:08.970 --> 32:10.754
Yeah.

32:10.798 --> 32:13.322
It's the initiation.
You got to blood in, blood out.

32:13.366 --> 32:15.150
Blood in, blood out.

32:15.194 --> 32:17.370
You kill somebody
to join a club.

32:18.414 --> 32:20.460
So?

32:20.503 --> 32:22.505
You were up next.

32:22.549 --> 32:24.768
Were you gonna do it?

32:25.813 --> 32:28.076
I don't know.Come on.

32:28.120 --> 32:29.773
Were you gonna do it or not?

32:29.817 --> 32:31.601
I don't know.

32:35.518 --> 32:38.173
Well, then you're a lucky man.

32:38.217 --> 32:40.784
'Cause all five of your
so-called tough guy friends

32:40.828 --> 32:43.048
ratted on each other.

32:43.091 --> 32:44.049
25 years.

32:44.092 --> 32:45.267
25 years.

32:45.311 --> 32:47.661
25 years. 25 years.

32:47.704 --> 32:50.620
Except for him, 'cause
he talked first, so...

32:50.664 --> 32:52.709
he's getting a break--
guess what he's doing.

32:52.753 --> 32:55.103
What?20 years.

32:55.147 --> 32:57.062
So they're all going to jail?Mm-hmm.

32:57.105 --> 32:59.455
They'll all be put away
till they're old men.

33:00.935 --> 33:02.676
So now it's time

33:02.719 --> 33:05.244
for youto choose.

33:05.287 --> 33:07.115
You gonna join
these knuckleheads

33:07.159 --> 33:10.510
and go off to prison until
you're an old man, too?

33:10.553 --> 33:14.514
Or are you gonna try to...
live the straight life?

33:14.557 --> 33:17.386
I'm gonna try living
the straight life. No doubt.

33:21.173 --> 33:23.305
I sure as hell hope so.

33:23.349 --> 33:27.135
And I'll sure as hell
be checking up on you
to make sure you do.

33:27.179 --> 33:28.441
So, um...

33:28.484 --> 33:30.834
am I... am I free to go?

33:30.878 --> 33:33.098
No.

33:33.141 --> 33:35.274
You're gonna do three months.

33:35.317 --> 33:37.058
For the gun.

33:37.102 --> 33:40.279
I want you to see the life
that you will have

33:40.322 --> 33:43.325
if you don't live
the straight life.

33:46.546 --> 33:48.548
♪

33:52.595 --> 33:54.293
MOLLY:
Doing some time

33:54.336 --> 33:57.600
should be good for him.Yeah. Should set
him right quick.

34:00.038 --> 34:02.910
Thank you, you know,
for doing all this.

34:02.953 --> 34:04.346
No. There's no way to know

34:04.390 --> 34:06.174
if your brother would've
actually went through with it.

34:06.218 --> 34:08.220
Though odds are...

34:08.263 --> 34:10.918
somebody's walking around
enjoying their life today

34:10.961 --> 34:14.530
who wouldn't be if you hadn't
come to me, so good on you.

34:14.574 --> 34:17.925
No, I mean for going
the extra mile.

34:17.968 --> 34:19.883
Nobody does that anymore.

34:19.927 --> 34:21.711
But it's what you do.

34:21.755 --> 34:23.844
I just do my job. Honest.

34:23.887 --> 34:26.499
No. Mm-mm. There's lots
of cops out there

34:26.542 --> 34:28.283
that would've told me
to piss off.

34:28.327 --> 34:30.024
But not you.

34:31.634 --> 34:35.595
Your brother's 16 years old,
and he's all you got left.

34:35.638 --> 34:38.032
Ironically, I'm kind of
in the same boat.

34:38.076 --> 34:40.469
And if I'm being
honest, I'm no angel,

34:40.513 --> 34:43.516
so that probably
played a part in this.

34:44.778 --> 34:46.736
All you got left?

34:46.780 --> 34:49.739
What, there's no
Mrs. Danny the Cop?

34:50.784 --> 34:52.568
:
No.

34:52.612 --> 34:55.658
No, Mrs. Danny the Cop died
a year and a half ago.

34:57.007 --> 34:59.619
My oldest son just
went off to college,

34:59.662 --> 35:02.752
and my youngest boy,
my 16-year-old, Sean,

35:02.796 --> 35:05.755
he's, uh... gonna follow
in his footsteps,

35:05.799 --> 35:07.583
so pretty soon it's
gonna be Danny the Cop

35:07.627 --> 35:09.629
alone in the house
all by himself.

35:09.672 --> 35:12.719
Mm. Sounds lonely.

35:12.762 --> 35:15.722
Well...Maybe you need,
like, a roommate?

35:15.765 --> 35:17.767
Yeah, I don't think
that's a good idea.

35:17.811 --> 35:20.205
Why? You just find someone
you're compatible with.

35:20.248 --> 35:22.598
Because I'm incompatible,
that's why.

35:22.642 --> 35:24.687
: I don't
know about that.

35:24.731 --> 35:27.125
I mean, look at us, right?
We're total opposites,

35:27.168 --> 35:28.865
and somehow, you know,

35:28.909 --> 35:31.738
we've got more in common
than people would think.

35:31.781 --> 35:36.177
Yeah. Yeah, we do have a few
little things in common. Maybe.

35:36.221 --> 35:38.745
One big thing, I think.

35:38.788 --> 35:40.747
What's that?

35:40.790 --> 35:42.575
I'm no angel either.

35:55.936 --> 35:57.807
Too soon?

35:59.853 --> 36:01.898
Yeah, maybe.

36:02.943 --> 36:04.858
I hear you.

36:06.381 --> 36:08.470
I should let you go.

36:14.563 --> 36:17.784
But I'm not gonna let you go,
if you know what I mean.

36:19.351 --> 36:21.570
You take it easy, Molly.

36:21.614 --> 36:23.050
Always...

36:23.093 --> 36:25.052
Danny the Cop.

36:32.712 --> 36:35.584
ABETEMARCO:
She's NYPD blue
through and through.

36:35.628 --> 36:37.020
You got my e

36:37.064 --> 36:39.022
You bet we did.

36:39.066 --> 36:41.721
That's some surveillance
sting you ran, Nicky.

36:41.764 --> 36:43.766
Five million family dinners
about nothing but cop talk,

36:43.810 --> 36:45.768
and you're sure
to learn something, right?

36:45.812 --> 36:49.381
I promise to never, ever
get on your bad side.

36:49.424 --> 36:51.209
Thanks, Anthony.

36:52.558 --> 36:54.255
He's right, you know.

36:54.299 --> 36:57.171
That was some good work.

36:57.215 --> 36:59.391
I'm really sorry.

36:59.434 --> 37:01.001
Oh, come on, no, you're not.

37:01.044 --> 37:04.222
You've earned
your right to gloat.

37:04.265 --> 37:07.660
The last thing
I want to do is gloat.

37:09.227 --> 37:11.272
That man was using you.

37:11.316 --> 37:13.361
Thanks...
for reminding me.

37:13.405 --> 37:15.320
Yes, Mom.You know what I mean.

37:15.363 --> 37:17.278
I know what you mean.

37:17.322 --> 37:19.802
And yes, part of me
is proud of myself

37:19.846 --> 37:22.588
for busting him, but...

37:22.631 --> 37:25.721
mostly I'm just hurt

37:25.765 --> 37:30.073
that a guy that I liked
didn't like me back.

37:30.117 --> 37:31.249
Nicky.

37:31.292 --> 37:33.599
I feel like such an idiot.

37:33.642 --> 37:37.472
Flaunting my relationship
around you like I'm some...

37:37.516 --> 37:39.866
woman of the world
when, in reality,

37:39.909 --> 37:43.435
I was... just
a gullible little girl.

37:43.478 --> 37:45.524
Don't do this.What?

37:45.567 --> 37:49.267
Don't start blaming yourself
for someone else's...

37:49.310 --> 37:51.051
terrible behavior.

37:51.094 --> 37:52.487
But I sh... Mm.

37:52.531 --> 37:55.055
You trusted him-- that's
what you're supposed to do.

37:55.098 --> 37:58.319
That's how you build
a real relationship.

37:58.363 --> 38:00.582
But this wasn't real.

38:01.627 --> 38:03.629
No, it wasn't,

38:03.672 --> 38:07.328
but... you learned a
lesson for the next guy.

38:07.372 --> 38:10.766
The next... much
younger guy.

38:12.072 --> 38:14.379
I knew you hated his age.He was, like, 50.

38:16.250 --> 38:18.383
You gonna be okay?

38:18.426 --> 38:21.995
Nothing some Netflix and a few
pints of ice cream can't fix.

38:28.393 --> 38:32.353
How about we go out
for your first martini instead?

38:32.397 --> 38:34.790
Extra dry with a twist, please.

38:35.965 --> 38:39.882
Okay, maybe it's not
your first martini.

38:41.362 --> 38:43.408
ESPINOZA:
It's a perfect
DNA match, sir.

38:43.451 --> 38:45.279
99.9%

38:45.323 --> 38:47.673
That's good work, Captain.

38:47.716 --> 38:51.416
And a welcome contrast
to last time you were up here.

38:51.459 --> 38:53.374
Much as I'd like to take
the credit, I can't.

38:53.418 --> 38:55.376
Hey, your cops, your collar.

38:55.420 --> 38:57.378
I appreciate that, sir,
but, um...

38:57.422 --> 38:59.337
it's an Officer Janko

38:59.380 --> 39:00.294
deserves the credit.

39:00.338 --> 39:01.382
As does

39:01.426 --> 39:02.470
her sergeant,

39:02.514 --> 39:04.167
for leading by example.

39:04.211 --> 39:05.778
And I'm not blowing smoke.

39:05.821 --> 39:07.388
Well, we'll see

39:07.432 --> 39:08.824
they get credit, too.

39:08.868 --> 39:09.956
There's someone else

39:09.999 --> 39:12.306
deserves it-- you, sir.

39:12.350 --> 39:13.916
This arrest is a direct result

39:13.960 --> 39:16.179
of your show of force
in my precinct.

39:16.223 --> 39:19.400
Now you are blowing smoke.

39:19.444 --> 39:22.185
No. He was the one
shooting the video

39:22.229 --> 39:25.363
while his crew verbally abused
my cops.

39:25.406 --> 39:27.365
What comes to mind?

39:27.408 --> 39:31.586
Success has a thousand mothers,
failure is an orphan.

39:31.630 --> 39:33.936
Anyway, good work,
and thank you.

39:33.980 --> 39:35.721
Sir.

39:35.764 --> 39:37.244
Gentlemen. Ma'am.

39:38.245 --> 39:40.421
Wow.

39:40.465 --> 39:41.727
Bushwick Butcher behind bars.

39:41.770 --> 39:43.337
Take a victory lap, boss.

39:43.381 --> 39:45.034
He doesn't take victory laps.

39:45.078 --> 39:47.036
Press'll eat it up,
huh, Garrett?

39:47.080 --> 39:48.690
Little buff on the image
can't hurt.

39:48.734 --> 39:50.431
If you believe them
when they say you're great,

39:50.475 --> 39:52.477
you have to believe them
when they say you suck.

39:52.520 --> 39:54.348
Zero-sum game.

39:54.392 --> 39:57.743
I'd like to say something
to all of you.

40:02.574 --> 40:06.012
It's my job to make sure
the NYPD doesn't get a black eye

40:06.055 --> 40:07.448
in the press, but...

40:07.492 --> 40:09.929
I'm starting to come
around to the idea

40:09.972 --> 40:12.410
that it's also my job

40:12.453 --> 40:15.456
to know that sometimes...

40:15.500 --> 40:18.024
getting a black eye
is worth it.

40:20.983 --> 40:22.507
That's it?

40:22.550 --> 40:24.334
That's it.

40:24.378 --> 40:25.727
Where's the "however"?

40:25.771 --> 40:26.728
There isn't one.

40:26.772 --> 40:29.862
Wow. That's a first.

40:32.125 --> 40:35.041
Thank you, Commissioner Moore.

